  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rapid response to the nutritional crisis in Opienge</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is part of the multi-sectoral emergency response &quot;humanitarian assistance to displaced populations&quot; for the Opienge health zone in Tshopo province. It proposes addressing the nutritional crisis in the area through support for the management of SAM (Severe Acute Malnutrition) in 100% of the health areas in the area, strengthening the management capacity at the level Health centers, sensitizing affected populations to preventing malnutrition, in particular through the promotion of the IYCF - Infant and Young Child Feeding, and strengthening the capacity of these populations to detect cases MAS. The proposal incorporates an EHA component - Water Hygiene and Sanitation - applying the approaches developed by the &quot;Wash in Nut&quot; strategy. In all sectors combined and considering the overlapping of certain activities, this project will cover 7,700 direct beneficiaries (by sector: 3,200 through nutrition and 7500 by EHA).</narrative>
  </description>
